      "title": "连词「还是」— Conjunction haishi (or / either...or...)",
      "explanation": "还是(háishi) means 'or' in questions and expresses a choice between two alternatives. Formula: A + 还是 + B? (Is it A or is it B?). Note: 还是(háishi) is used in questions asking for a choice, while 或者(huòzhě) is used in statements. Example: 你(nǐ)喝茶(hē chá)还是(háishi)喝咖啡(hē kā fēi)？(Do you drink tea or coffee?)",
